By Esther Egbe


Super Eagles and Enyimba safe hand, Ikechukwu Ezenwa explained recently that his team mates  picked six points in the two games they have  played so far and hoped they maintain focus in the coming games.

Ezenwa told National Daily that he is fine, fit and ready to play, I give all glory to God for quick recovery. I am back in training and doing my best”.

Enyimba FC goal keeper added  that the match against Madagascar was not going to be an easy one because the team is going to put up a fight and not go down easily.


He concluded that the support of the fans and the hard work the Super Eagles was going to put in, he hopes for  a victory.




			
